thread.title: Tigers finish in bottom half at Raccoon River Conference Meet
thread.title_full: Tigers finish in bottom half at Raccoon River Conference Meet

author: hdmoadmin
title: Tigers finish in bottom half at Raccoon River Conference Meet
text:
2:56 pm - October 14, 2015 Tigers finish in bottom half at Raccoon River Conference Meet A-D-M's Sydney Engleman, shown running in Adel earlier this year, took 17th overall in the girls' race on Tuesday. PHOTO BY CLINT COLE/DALLAS COUNTY NEWS 
Staff Report 
The A-D-M boys’ and girls’ cross country teams traveled to Boone on Tuesday for the Raccoon River Conference Cross Country Meet. Both teams finished in the bottom half in their races. 
The girls had a team score of 104, good enough for fifth place in the seven-team field while the boys had a team score of 161, good enough for sixth place. Ballard took first in the girls’ race and Winterset took first in the boys’ race. 
The A-D-M girls had four runners finish in the top 25. They were led by Sadie Juergens, a freshman who took 13th place overall with a time of 21:12. 
Sophomore Sydney Engleman took 17th place overall with a time of 21:34 on the 5,000 meter course while fellow sophomore Ashlie Hauf took 22nd place with a time of 21:57. Lydia Weighner, a senior, took 25th place with a time of 22:19 while sophomore Kylie Hauf took 27th place overall with a time of 22:22 to round out the scoring for the Tigers. 
Senior Katie Klocke and sophomore Jesse Howard also competed at the meet for the Tigers. Klocke took 30th place with a time of 22:52 and Howard took 36th place with a time of 23:55. 
The A-D-M boys only had one runner finish in the top 20. A-D-M freshman Iain Newman led the Tigers with a 19th-place finish and a time of 17:42 overall. 
After Newman finished, five Tigers in a row crossed the finish line in 34th through 38th places. Junior Brady Meier took 34th with a time of 18:49, sophomore Phillip Hlas took 35th with a time of 18:51, Eli Schwarzkopf took 36th with a time of 18:55, Kodi Jensen took 37th with a time of 19:00 and Micah Moyer took 38th with a time of 19:06. 
Nolan Harsh, a freshman at A-D-M, also competed in the meet for the Tigers, taking 46th place with a time of 20:16 on the course in Boone. 
The Tigers will compete next at the State Qualifying Meet at Glenwood Lake Park in Glenwood. The meet on Thursday, Oct. 22 will begin at 4 p.m.
